This paper deals with radio resource management and interference management in wireless networks, which are topics related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the allocation of bandwidth and the optimization of signal-to-interference plus noise ratio (SINR), which are topics related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also mentions the intensification of bandwidth utilization, which is related to multimedia systems and applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. The paper proposes a scheme for improving system capacity and reducing outage probability, which are topics related to control systems and robotics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with interference management, which is related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible category.
